  sodium: 880 mg
cuisine: North America
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
time required: 35 minutes
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/crispy-buffalo-spiced-chicken-677409b4893e50c2a80a573a
---

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and
dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces.
Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2},
separating whites from greens.

> Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces or trim green beans if necessary. Save carrots
> for another use.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}, half the
@Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until golden
brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> Swap in broccoli or green beans for carrots. Roast on top rack, 15-20 minutes for
> broccoli or 12-15 minutes for green beans.

While carrots roast, place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to
cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve 1⁄2 cup potato cooking liquid; drain and return potatoes to pot. Mash with
one packet of @Sour Cream{4.5%tablespoon} (two packets for 4 servings) and @butter{1%TBSP}
(2 TBSP for 4) with a #potato masher{} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved
potato cooking liquid as needed. Stir in half the scallion greens. Season with salt
and pepper. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt
and pepper.

Place @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a shallow #microwave-safe dish{}.
Microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup},
@Frank's Seasoning Blend{1/4%ounce}, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Brush one packet sour cream (two packets for 4) onto tops of chicken in a thin layer.
Working one piece at a time, dip brushed sides of chicken into panko mixture,
pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides). Place chicken, coated sides up,
on a second, lightly oiled baking sheet.

Roast chicken on middle rack until browned and cooked through, ~{15-18%minutes}.
Transfer to a #plate{} to rest.

While chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Blue Cheese Dressing{1.5%ounce},
scallion whites, and remaining sour cream.

Divide carrots, mashed potatoes, and chicken between plates. Top chicken with
blue cheese sauce, remaining scallion greens, and @?Hot Sauce{1%teaspoon} if desired.
Serve with any remaining blue cheese sauce on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.